author: National Geographic
description:
Contrary to popular belief, scrolling on social media doesn't lead to literal "brain rot." The true process of brain decay is a complex story involving cellular breakdown, bacteria, and preservation. And some brains, it turns out, can last far longer than we ever imagined. Learn more about brain rot at: https://on.natgeo.com/4oSvI1b

Host: Sarah Gibbens
